@endnode
@node PacketSelect "Packet Selection"

    Packet Selection.

    @{" Open Packet    " link OpenPacket}  Open packet for reading.
    @{" Config AmiQWK  " link Config_Main}  Configure AmiQWK II.
    @{" About AmiQWK   " link AboutAQ}  Information about AmiQWK II.
    @{" Help!          " link Help}  Help with AmiQWK II.
    @{" Rename Packet  " link RenamePacket}  Rename a QWKMail packet.
    @{" Delete Packet  " link DeletePacket}  Delete a QWKMail packet.
    @{" Quit and Exit  " link QuitAndExit}  Quit and exit AmiQWK.

    @{" Main Help Menu " link Main}  Return to the main help menu.

@endnode
@node OpenPacket "Open Packet"
    Pressing this gadget will display a file requester. Use it to select
the packet you want to read.

    The directory to be searched and the pattern to search for to
locate .QWK packets can be set in the @{"configuration" link Config_Main} section.

@endnode
@node AboutAQ "About AmiQWK II"

    AmiQWK II is a BBS offline mail reader compatible with the QWKMail
offline mail format developed by Mark 'Sparky' Herring.

    Pressing this gadget displays important information about AmiQWK II,
including version number, compile date, Copyright notice, Where to send
bug reports, etc.

    AmiQWK II was written by Jim Dawson and is copyright (c) 1992-1993 by
Jim Dawson. All Rights Reserved.

@endnode
@node help "Online Help"

    AmiQWK II supports online help using AmigaGuide from Commodore.

